- tCompeting Competencies: The Struggle for Authority in Deut 17:8-13 in Comparative Perspective / rSamuel, Harald -- tPost mortem Mosi: Conceptualizing Leadership in the Book of Joshua / rKrause, Joachim J. -- tGideon, a Liminal Leader: The Transformation of Leadership Concepts in Judg 6-8 / rSchulz, Sarah / Schäfer, Manuel -- tThe Structures of Offices in the Heroic Narratives and Judge Narratives and Their Literary-Historical Development / rFocken, Friedrich-Emanuel -- tSamuel's Political Career / rBezzel, Hannes -- tSaul, the Charismatic King: Concepts of Political Leadership in 1Sam 11 / rMüller, Reinhard -- tFrom David to Solomon, from Crisis to Leadership / rSteiner, Till Magnus -- tProphetic Leadership in the Books of Kings / rSauerwein, Ruth -- tThe Unique Status of Jehu's Dynasty / rRobker, Jonathan Miles -- tDebating Authority - Concepts of Leadership in the Pentateuch and the Former Prophets: A Synthesis / rPyschny, Katharina / Schulz, Sarah -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex of Ancient Sources  aHuman leadership is a multifaceted topic in the Hebrew Bible. This holds true not only for the final form of the texts, but also for their literary history. A large range of distributions emerges from the successive sharpening or modification of different aspects of leadership. While some of them are combined to a complex figuration of leadership, others remain reserved for certain individuals. Furthermore, it can be considered a consensus within the scholarly debate, that concepts of leadership have a certain connection to the history of ancient Israel which is, though, hard to ascertain. Up to now, all these aspects of (human) leadership have been treated in a rather isolated manner. Against this background,the volume focuses on the different concepts of leadership in the Pentateuch and the Former Prophets. Concepts like "priest", "prophet", "judge", and "king" are examined in a literary, (religious-/tradition-) historical and theological perspective. Hence, the volume contributes to biblical theology and sheds new light on the redaction/reception history of the Pentateuch and the Former Prophets. Not least, it provides valuable insights into the history of religious and/or political "authorities" in Israel and Early Judaism(s).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Sep 2018) 4aFormer Prophets. 4aFrühere Propheten. 4aHerrschaft. 4aLeadership. 4aPentateuch.1 aPyschny, Katharina, eeditor.1 aSchulz, Sarah, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishz978311060424508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2018z9783110603248oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831105427520 cprintz978311054070340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110543391423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110543391.jpg  a978-3-11-060424-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGFb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017